## 📌 1. History & Features of Java

### 🕰️ History

* Java was developed by **James Gosling** at **Sun Microsystems** in **1995**
* Originally called **Oak** → later renamed to Java
* Now owned by **Oracle Corporation**

---

### 🌟 Key Features of Java (VERY IMPORTANT)

#### 1. Platform Independent (WORA)

* **Write Once, Run Anywhere**
* Java code compiles to **bytecode**
* Runs on any system with JVM

---

#### 2. Object-Oriented

* Based on OOP principles:

  * Encapsulation
  * Inheritance
  * Polymorphism
  * Abstraction

---

#### 3. Simple

* Easy syntax (similar to C++)
* No pointers (reduces complexity)

---

#### 4. Secure

* No direct memory access
* Bytecode verification
* Runs inside JVM sandbox

---

#### 5. Robust

* Strong memory management
* Exception handling
* Garbage collection

---

#### 6. Multithreaded

* Supports concurrent execution using threads

---

#### 7. Portable

* Same bytecode runs everywhere

---

#### 8. High Performance

* Uses **JIT (Just-In-Time compiler)**

---

#### 9. Distributed

* Supports networking (RMI, sockets)

---

## 📌 2. JDK, JRE, JVM

This is one of the **most asked interview questions**.

---

### 🔹 JVM (Java Virtual Machine)

* Executes Java bytecode
* Platform dependent

#### Responsibilities:

* Memory management
* Garbage collection
* Bytecode execution

---

### 🔹 JRE (Java Runtime Environment)

* Provides runtime environment to run Java programs

👉 Includes:

* JVM
* Libraries

---

### 🔹 JDK (Java Development Kit)

* Used to develop Java programs

👉 Includes:

* JRE
* Compiler (`javac`)
* Tools (debugger, etc.)

---

### 🎯 Relationship (IMPORTANT)

👉 **JDK = JRE + Development Tools**
👉 **JRE = JVM + Libraries**

---

## 📌 3. Data Types

### 🔹 Primitive Data Types (8 types)

| Type    | Size    | Example    |
| ------- | ------- | ---------- |
| byte    | 1 byte  | 10         |
| short   | 2 bytes | 200        |
| int     | 4 bytes | 1000       |
| long    | 8 bytes | 100000L    |
| float   | 4 bytes | 10.5f      |
| double  | 8 bytes | 20.99      |
| char    | 2 bytes | 'A'        |
| boolean | 1 bit   | true/false |

---

### 🔹 Non-Primitive Data Types

* String
* Arrays
* Classes
* Interfaces

👉 These store **reference**, not actual value

---

## 📌 4. Variables & Scope

### 🔹 Types of Variables

#### 1. Local Variables

* Declared inside method/block
* Must be initialized before use

---

#### 2. Instance Variables

* Declared inside class (outside method)
* Each object gets its own copy

---

#### 3. Static Variables

* Declared with `static`
* Shared among all objects

---

### 🔹 Scope

| Variable Type | Scope               |
| ------------- | ------------------- |
| Local         | Within method/block |
| Instance      | Entire object       |
| Static        | Entire class        |

---

## 📌 5. Type Casting

Converting one data type into another.

---

### 🔹 1. Implicit Casting (Widening)

* Smaller → Larger type
* Done automatically

```java
int a = 10;
double b = a;
```

---

### 🔹 2. Explicit Casting (Narrowing)

* Larger → Smaller type
* Done manually

```java
double a = 10.5;
int b = (int) a;
```

---

⚠️ May cause **data loss**

---

## 📌 6. Operators

---

### 🔹 1. Arithmetic Operators

```java
