```

---

### 🔹 2. Relational Operators

```java
==  !=  >  <  >=  <=
```

---

### 🔹 3. Logical Operators

```java
&&  ||  !
```

---

### 🔹 4. Assignment Operators

```java
=  +=  -=  *=  /=
```

---

### 🔹 5. Unary Operators

```java
++  --  !
```

---

### 🔹 6. Bitwise Operators (less common but asked)

```java
&  |  ^  ~  <<  >>
```

---

### 🔹 7. Ternary Operator

```java
condition ? value1 : value2;
```

Example:

```java
int max = (a > b) ? a : b;
```

---

# 🎯 Interview Summary (Must Remember)

If interviewer asks “Basics of Java”, say:

> Java is a platform-independent, object-oriented programming language developed by James Gosling. It follows the WORA principle using JVM. The core basics include data types, variables, operators, type casting, and Java runtime components like JDK, JRE, and JVM.

